nce 2014,affects metabolismand is believed to help with endurance in physical activity.\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2278, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The substance\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"a heart medication\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"2014,affects metabolismand\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"endurance\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2256}, {\"ngram\": \"physical activity\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was thrust into the global spotlight during the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics after star Russian figure skater Kamila Valieva was handed afour-year banfor a positive test ahead of the event.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2370, \"end\": 2377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9924013061474408, \"rank\": 0.006054430978761041, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kamila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the global spotlight\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2318}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2358}, {\"ngram\": \"a positive test\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the case of the Chinese swimmers, CHINADA decided the athletes should not be held responsible for the results after its \\\"immediate\\\" investigation concluded the swimmers were inadvertently exposed to the substance through contamination, its statement said, according to Xinhua.\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2492, \"end\": 2499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.996193898512052, \"rank\": 0.0038199968328975972, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.612561254294525e-34, \"text\": \"Xinhua\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2484}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2517}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2538}, {\"ngram\": \"the results\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2585}, {\"ngram\": \"its \\\"immediate\\\" investigation\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2644}, {\"ngram\": \"the substance\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2688}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"its statement\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2725}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In its statement Saturday, WADA said it was notified in June 2021 of CHINADA's ruling on the swimmers who had tested positive earlier that year.\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2898, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its statement\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2770}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 2810, \"to\": 2814}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA's ruling\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2839}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As part of its review, WADA collected additional, unpublished scientific information on TMZ and consulted with independent scientific experts to test the contamination theory and also whether low doses of TMZ could have benefited the athletes during a swimming competition event,\\\" the agency said in its statement.\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 3215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2989, \"end\": 2992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3657346576124e-12, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}, {\"begin\": 3106, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3657346576124e-12, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2904, \"to\": 2908}, {\"ngram\": \"its review\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2928}, {\"ngram\": \"additional, unpublished scientific information\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"independent scientific experts\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3042}, {\"ngram\": \"the contamination theory\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3075}, {\"ngram\": \"low doses\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3102}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"a swimming competition event\", \"from\": 3151, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"the agency\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3192}, {\"ngram\": \"its statement\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"WADA ultimately concluded that it was not in a position to disprove the possibility that contamination was the source of TMZ and it was compatible with the analytical data in the file,\\\" the statement said, adding that \\\"in all transparency\\\" it shared its findings with internal and external investigators.\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3522, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 3218, \"t